column5: Just to let folks know the bass fishing on the gog is alive and well, lots of bass being caught and they seem to look OK,accually they seem happier now that theres more room to swim.
what part were u fishing on? good to hear!

I heard that there was some good fish caught in the river area,near the north end of the lake,just watch at high speed you dont hit a dead carp,it will tear off your transducer,thats what happened to a guy i know...just heard that today.....there is still hundreds of dead ones so carefull.....cheers  good news to hear that they are still there alive and well....
Very good news...  are there still people cleaning up those dead carps? or it was only for those washed up to the shore?
The cleanup continues, not sure how a transducer can get riped off, as it should be higher than the bottom of the boat, or he was backtrolling really really fast.
